    • Method Detail

      • linkReference

        public void linkReference(E from,
                          Object to,
                          String label,
                          String oppositeLabel,
                          boolean isContainment)
        Links from and to by creating a mapped reference.

        Note that to can be an element of the source model that has to be resolved (declarative binding), or an element of the target model that has been created by the rule (multi-binding rule). If to is in the source model and cannot be resolved (because the corresponding target element has not been created yet) a proxy link (see AbstractATLTransformationHelper.createProxyLink(Object, Object, String, String, boolean)) is created that will be resolved later (see AbstractATLTransformationHelper.resolveProxies(Object, Object)).

        The default implementation of this method checks if to is in the source or target model. If it is part of the source model it checks whether the element can be resolved and creates a concrete/proxy link accordingly. If the element is part of the target model a concrete link is created.

        Overrides the default implementation by using isSourceElement(Object) and isTargetElement(Object) to check if an element is in the source or the target model.

        Overrides:
        linkReference in class AbstractATLTransformationHelper<E,E>
        Parameters:
        from - the tail (in the target model) of the link to create
        to - the head of the link to create (from the source or the target model)
        label - the label of the link to create
        oppositeLabel - the label of the opposite reference if it exists
        isContainment - true if the reference is a containment, false otherwise
        See Also:
        AbstractATLTransformationHelper.linkReference(Object, Iterable, String, String, boolean)

      • isTargetElement

        protected abstract boolean isTargetElement(E element)
        Checks if the provided element is in the target model.

        This method is specific to InPlaceATLTransformationHelper that uses the same ModelDatastore for source and target models. The transformation has to check if an element is in the target model in order to create concrete/proxy links and resolve elements.

        Parameters:
        element - the element to check
        Returns:
        true if element is in the target model, false otherwise
        See Also:
        AbstractATLTransformationHelper.createConcreteLink(Object, Object, String, String, boolean), AbstractATLTransformationHelper.createProxyLink(Object, Object, String, String, boolean), AbstractATLTransformationHelper.resolve(Object), AbstractATLTransformationHelper.resolveProxies(Object, Object)

      • isSourceElement

        protected boolean isSourceElement(E element)
        Checks if the provided element is in the source model.

        This method should return the opposite of isTargetElement(Object). It is specific to InPlaceATLTransformationHelper that uses the same ModelDatastore for source and target models. The transformation has to check if an element is in the source model in order to create concrete/proxy links and resolve elements.

        Parameters:
        element - the element to check
        Returns:
        true if the element is in the source model, false otherwise
        See Also:
        AbstractATLTransformationHelper.createConcreteLink(Object, Object, String, String, boolean), AbstractATLTransformationHelper.createProxyLink(Object, Object, String, String, boolean), AbstractATLTransformationHelper.resolve(Object), AbstractATLTransformationHelper.resolveProxies(Object, Object)
